# V07 Frontend — environment configuration
#
# Copy this file to `.env` (or `.env.local`) and fill in any of the values
# below to enable optional features. Vars must be prefixed with VITE_ to be
# exposed to the client bundle.
#
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Web search provider
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# The web-search toggle in the input bar uses one of four providers,
# chosen automatically based on which env vars are set. Override with
# VITE_SEARCH_PROVIDER if you want to force a specific one.
#
# Resolution order (first that's configured wins):
#   1. VITE_SEARCH_PROVIDER (explicit override: tavily | searxng | duckduckgo | wikipedia)
#   2. tavily   — if VITE_TAVILY_API_KEY is set
#   3. searxng  — if VITE_SEARXNG_URL is set
#   4. duckduckgo (default, zero setup; limited to instant answers)
#
# Wikipedia is always the last-resort fallback when nothing else works.
#
# ── Option A: Tavily (recommended for real-time, AI-optimised results) ──
# Free tier: 1,000 searches/month, no credit card. Sign up at
#   https://app.tavily.com  →  copy your API key here.
# Routed through the Vite dev proxy at /api/tavily so CORS works.
#
# VITE_TAVILY_API_KEY=tvly-xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
#
# ── Option B: Self-hosted SearXNG (unlimited, no key, full control) ──
# Run a local instance with:
#   docker run --rm -d -p 8888:8080 \
#     -e SEARXNG_SECRET=$(openssl rand -hex 32) \
#     searxng/searxng
# Then set VITE_SEARXNG_URL to where it's reachable. The Vite proxy
# at /api/searxng forwards requests to this URL.
#
# IMPORTANT: enable JSON output in the SearXNG instance settings.yml:
#   search:
#     formats: [html, json]
#
# VITE_SEARXNG_URL=http://localhost:8888
#
# ── Option C: Force a specific provider regardless of keys ──
# Useful for testing or forcing the fallback chain.
#
# VITE_SEARCH_PROVIDER=duckduckgo
